subject: College Athletics
lead_paragraph: Jinelle Zaugg scored twice and Jessie Vetter made 33 saves to help the two-time defending champion Wisconsin (29-8-3) beat Harvard, 4-1, in the N.C.A.A. women’s Frozen Four semifinals in Duluth, Minn. Top-ranked Harvard (32-2-0) lost for the first time in 22 games.
